Bournemouth have officially extended Harry Wilson’s loan deal which will see him remain at Vitality Stadium until the end of the 2019/20 season. Wilson current deal was set to expire on June 30 but he will see out the season due to the coronavirus pandemic that has brought football to a halt. The 23-year-old will be a massive boost for the team as they return to their relegation battle – he put on impressive displays in his first season, scoring seven goals in 27 appearances. Bournemouth will welcome Crystal Palace at home on June 20 and will look battle it out to remain in topflight while they are currently level on points with Watford. Wilson made one appearance for Liverpool in the FA cup against Plymouth back in 2017.